TW_outfit_011.description: The Wraith ventured in mangrove swamps, covering his arms in mud. He scavenged materials from crashed vehicles to cover the rest of his body.

TW_outfit_014.name: High-Vis Scraps
TW_outfit_014.description: Working at a high-risk location requires some mitigating precautions.

TW_outfit_014_01.name: High-Vis Scraps (Deep Rift)
TW_outfit_014_01.description: Living in a waking nightmare requires some mitigating precautions.

TW_outfit_017.description: Every morning, Ojomo would leave several bowls of cat food around the garage.

TW_outfit_01_03.description: The incessant croaking throughout the swamp made him wonder… what sounds do frogs make when flayed alive

TW_outfit_01_04.name: Bad Omen (5th Anniversary)

TW_outfit_022.name: Mind Haunter
TW_outfit_022.description: The sharp fingers released him at last, and he realized he was somewhere new.

TW_W007.name: The Heart of Miss Smithson
TW_W007.description: His pupil’s young heart beats under the bell’s dome, delivering an ominous pulse.

TW_W008.name: Blood Reaver
TW_W008.description: A rusted blade that's scraped and sawed its way through flesh and bone.

TW_W009.name: Oaken Backbone

TW_W009_01.name: Unknown Backbone
TW_W009_01.description: A weapon crafted from an unidentified species.

TW_W010.description: Twisted license plates curl over a rusted pipe; a memory of the sights once seen, and the many who were lost along the way… by his hands.

TW_W011.name: Raw Spine
TW_W011.description: A reptilian spine of decomposing flesh made from his previous kills.

TW_W012.name: Axe of Reprisal
TW_W012.description: A vicious weapon pieced together with refuse from the scrap heap, and the skull of a man who deserved everything he got.

TW_W015_CS.description: This bizarre sub-clone results from an unknown technology combined with organic material.

TW_W017.description: Ojomo discovered the remains of a cat under the discarded metal and gave it a proper burial.

TW_W018.name: Sweet Blade
TW_W018.description: A sharp blade coated in sour candy.

TW_W019.description: He watched the car get crushed, metal and bones merging while carefully polishing the antlers.

TW_W01_03.description: A peculiar artifact from the muddy depths of the pond, it reeks of decomposing swamp life.

TW_W01_04.description: The teeth of death lie on the Azarovs skull and spine.

TW_W021.name: Adorned Axe
TW_W021.description: Everything would be all right from now on, and his grandmother would always be with him.

TW_W022.name: Adorned Spine
TW_W022.description: Together they forged ahead, their connection strong and unspoken.

TW_W03_03.name: Sanguine Blade
TW_W03_03.description: A sword forged in fire and blood.

TW_W04_03.name: Spine Candy
TW_W04_03.description: Each vertebra from the spine and skull of an unfortunate victim dripped with blood, forming perfect stripes of crimson, like a candy-cane.

UK_Body007.description: The skirmishes became a regular danger to citizens as collateral damage added up.

UK_Body007_01.description: Good camouflage for the Emerald Isle.

UK_Body007_02.name: Mood Killer
UK_Body007_02.description: When The Entity gifted him with this romantic ensemble, it felt like a cruel trick.

UK_Body009.description: He wore thick overalls, equipped with a utility belt with fresh catches and sharp hooks. As he scouted the harbor, he found his elusive bounty unloading a crate of giant squids.

UK_Body010.name: Moth-ridden Duster
UK_Body010.description: They’ve made a mess of his jacket. Should have used mothballs.

UK_Body013.description: This brace, inspired by locomotive engineering was more comfortable than he expected.

VE_033.name: Dead by Daylight Issue #3
VE_033.description: FRANK and JULIE raise the stakes ever higher as THE LEGION continue to unleash chaos on Ormond. But can JOEY resist the call of THE ENTITY, or is it too late to escape his fate? Cover art by Jesus Hervas.

VE_038.description: Not the time to be abducted by aliens.

VE_040.name: Dead by Daylight Issue #4
VE_040.description: You never forget your first love, or your first kill – and for SUSIE the two will be eternally intertwined in the Realm of THE ENTITY. An act of teenage rebellion spins out of control, and life for THE LEGION will never be the same… Cover art by Dani & Brad Simpson.

VE_041.name: Dead by Daylight Graphic Novel
VE_041.description: When the rebellious FRANK crashes into the lives of JULIE, JOEY and SUSIE, together they’ll unleash bloody chaos onto the sleepy, dead-end town of Ormond. Witness the terrifying origins of THE LEGION. Cover art by Jae Lee.

VI_001.name: Iron Entity Abstract
VI_001.description: A conceptual model of The Entity. The light rusting may be intentional.

VI_002.name: Bronze Entity Abstract
VI_002.description: A conceptual model of The Entity. Though the metal remains strong, it rings hollow within.

VI_003.name: Gold Entity Abstract
VI_003.description: A conceptual model of The Entity. Though lacking magnetism, the carving attracts itself to certain people.

VI_004.name: Astral Entity Abstract
VI_004.description: A conceptual model of The Entity. Though beautiful, it evokes anxiety in those who hold it.

VI_005.name: Peak 22 Keychain
VI_005.description: Memorabilia from an ambitious, yet doomed-to-fail, social media company.

VI_006.name: Hawaiian Slice
VI_006.description: A highly controversial statement that yes, pineapple belongs on pizza.

VI_007.name: Kate's Guitar
VI_007.description: An acoustic guitar, perfectly tuned and engraved with flowers.

VI_008.name: Kate Denson Figurine
VI_008.description: A hopeful songbird, Kate lifted others' spirits when all seemed lost.

VI_009.name: Music of Pearl
VI_009.description: A music note formed from mother of pearl, glittering with luminosity.

VI_010.name: Horse Head
VI_010.description: A grotesque trophy, taken from the remains of a cavalry unit.

VI_011.name: Bunny Hood Doll
VI_011.description: A worn-down doll, soiled, reeking, and cherished above all.

VI_012.name: Tree of Life
VI_012.description: A symbol of life, though from another perspective, it's the vessel that ferries one to death.

VI_013.name: Ouroboros
VI_013.description: And so, as it ends, it begins.

VI_014.name: Triple Moon
VI_014.description: A symbol of birth, life, and death. The finality of the waning moon seems incongruous in The Entity's realm.

VI_015.name: Flower of Life
VI_015.description: A key to unlocking sacred wisdom or a trifling bauble

VI_016.name: Peak 22 thermos
VI_016.description: Distributed to employees to boost morale in lieu of a bonus.

VI_017.name: Simulation Terror
VI_017.description: The critics agree: “Simulation Terror is a terror to read!”

VI_018.name: Rusted Horseshoe
VI_018.description: The few who hold a remnant of hope and innocence believe it bestows luck.

VI_019.name: Killer Tunes
VI_019.description: Every great murder has a soundtrack.

VI_020.name: Screaming Speakers
VI_020.description: There was a discordance to the damaged speakers that gave them a unique sound all to themselves.

VI_021.name: Vaporius Hexahedron
VI_021.description: A finely crafted container that stimulates a wisp of ever-changing Fog.

VI_022.name: Timekeeper
VI_022.description: A relic that's incapable of measuring time in this realm.

VI_023.name: Forsaken Child
VI_023.description: The trinket of a child, alone, cold, and terrified.

VI_024.name: Reclusive Scavenger
VI_024.description: The trinket of a teenager, searching for a morsel.

VI_025.name: Clever Hunter
VI_025.description: The trinket of a woman, taking fate into her own hands.

VI_026.name: Ruthless Predator
VI_026.description: The trinket of a killer, stalking those who approach her home.

VI_027.name: Deadly Terror
VI_027.description: The trinket of a monster, asserting dominance over all in her forest.

VI_028.name: Child's Melody
VI_028.description: With quiet confidence, Kate picked up the guitar.

VI_029.name: Strummer's Melody
VI_029.description: Sometimes Kate's fingers missed a chord, but it didn't deter her.

VI_030.name: Singer's Melody
VI_030.description: Kate's voice had a natural cadence that made people want to listen.

VI_031.name: Musician's Melody
VI_031.description: Kate combined the guitar with her voice, as if it was a single part of her.

VI_032.name: Songbird's Melody
VI_032.description: There was a spark of hope that Kate kept in her voice, wherever she went. It was of greater importance than she'd know.

VI_033.name: Unlimited Entity-Wide
VI_033.description: Hello? The mobile realm awaits your sacrifice.

WA_001.name: Seal of Metatron

WA_002.name: Vic Viper
WA_002.description: A tribute to the white-and-blue star fighter tasked with saving the galaxy from an evil Bacterian Empire.

WA_003.description: A crumbling cake emanating a dark and ominous force. "Happy anniversary! Here’s to four years of spilling blood together!"

WA_004.name: 4th Anniversary
WA_004.description: A tribute to celebrate the fourth year of Dead by Daylight.

Witch_outfit_001.name: Sapling Siren
Witch_outfit_001.description: The transformation into full plant creature is almost complete. Just a few more souls to produce the light and energy required…

Witch_outfit_002.name: Wood Witch
Witch_outfit_002.description: As old as the forest itself. A fossil. A preserved shell. The petrification process has begun. Only the blood of the living can reverse it.

Witch_outfit_003.name: Mud Medusa
Witch_outfit_003.description: The veined Medusa has relished in the darkness of the swamp, growing stronger and stronger, day by day.

Witch_outfit_004.name: Weathered Crone
Witch_outfit_004.description: A misshapen, discolored swamp creature, with a deadly claw for a hand.

Witch_outfit_005.description: A misshapen, discolored swamp creature, with a deadly claw for a hand.

Witch_outfit_006.description: A misshapen, discolored swamp creature, with a deadly claw for a hand.

Witch_outfit_006_01.name: Queen of the Mire
Witch_outfit_006_01.description: One of the many possible lives denied to Lisa Sherwood by her captors.

Witch_outfit_007.name: Weathered Crone
Witch_outfit_007.description: A misshapen, discolored swamp creature, with a deadly claw for a hand.

Witch_outfit_008.name: Weathered Crone
Witch_outfit_008.description: A misshapen, discolored swamp creature, with a deadly claw for a hand.

Witch_outfit_009.name: Weathered Crone
Witch_outfit_009.description: A misshapen, discolored swamp creature, with a deadly claw for a hand.

Witch_outfit_010.name: Red Sap
Witch_outfit_010.description: As days go by, she becomes the wilderness.

Witch_outfit_011.name: Birch Twigs
Witch_outfit_011.description: As days go by, she becomes the wilderness.

WI_Body006.name: Tattered Silk Dress
WI_Body006.description: The dress has seen better days, but still retains a semblance of the beauty that it once possessed, much like its wearer.

WI_Body006_01.name: Grandmother's Gown
WI_Body006_01.description: It was a family heirloom, passed down through the generations. It was meant to be hers one day.

WI_Body007.name: Slithering Den
WI_Body007.description: Wrapped in the remains of a boa constrictor, teeming with filth and moss—that which the swamp provides shall never be returned.

WI_Body008.name: Molten Limbs
WI_Body008.description: Her organs melted and fused into a burning mass.

WI_Body009.name: Teratoma
WI_Body009.description: Something, or someone, grew within her, its bones protruding, limbs reaching for freedom from the prison of flesh.

WI_Body010.name: Bark Crust
WI_Body010.description: A deep outrage surged and stiffened her body, transforming her limbs into a hard, crust.

WI_Body011.name: Foul Scales
WI_Body011.description: The smell alone was nearly enough to kill.

WI_Body012.name: Gnawed Wood
WI_Body012.description: Insects had burrowed their way through her emaciated body.

WI_Body014.name: Wooden Ribcage
WI_Body014.description: Her grandmother told her a story of a moss-covered woman with a glowing heart.

WI_Body015.name: Marsh Blossoms
WI_Body015.description: Instead of simply being sapped, she found ways to take power back. A grim symbiosis.

WI_Body017.name: Arachnid Agility
WI_Body017.description: She would scurry softly along the ceiling, ambushing them when there was no chance of escape.

WI_Body01_03.name: Overwatered
WI_Body01_03.description: Vegetation grew deep within her husk, tearing her apart in a beautiful red and green glow.

WI_Body01_WinterEvent2017.name: Frosty Eyes
WI_Body01_WinterEvent2017.description: Heart chilling eyes of the cold-blooded.

WI_Body03_01.name: Venom Veins
WI_Body03_01.description: Exterior veins have developed across the surface of the skin, most likely supporting the twisted, snake-like protrusions from the side of the skull.

WI_Body04.name: Blooming Seed Core
WI_Body04.description: This hybrid reaction is also the start of the reproductive process, causing new, unexpected plant life to form.

WI_Body04_01.name: Blooming Seed Core (Ice Blue)
WI_Body04_01.description: The seed core is the central component in converting light into the chemical energy required to perform the key functions of a plant creature.

WI_Hair006.name: Hair Rings
WI_Hair006.description: The mud has been wiped away and the Hag's hair is held off her face with rings and clips.

WI_Hair006_01.name: Pearly Hair Wrap
WI_Hair006_01.description: Her grandmother spoke of people in big cities who dressed in luxury every day.

WI_Hair007.name: Fangtasmagoria
WI_Hair007.description: Ornamented of bone and blood, with teeth formed of the serpent. The result of one whose humanity has long been lost to rage and revenge.

WI_Hair008.name: Ember Locks
WI_Hair008.description: Her charred dreads could not cover the painful, serum-filled blisters on her head.

WI_Hair009.name: Twin Terror
WI_Hair009.description: The mark of power carved into her forehead allowed her to access unnatural abilities, but with it came a repulsive transformation.

WI_Hair010.name: Knotted Crown
WI_Hair010.description: Damp soil grumbled, and roots sprung from the ground.

WI_Hair011.name: Aquatic Visage
WI_Hair011.description: Her face resembled a fish, her body almost human… a true horror from the depths.

WI_Hair012.name: Oozing Bulb
WI_Hair012.description: Pollen continued to seep from the growth on her head.

WI_Hair014.name: Wooden Charm
WI_Hair014.description: Her grandmother taught her how to create wooden charms out of twigs and branches.

WI_Hair015.name: Lilypad Cap
WI_Hair015.description: The local flora took its nutrients from her, just as her captors once had.

WI_Hair016.name: Hag's Mask
WI_Hair016.description: A mask she found herself wearing at the masquerade ball.

WI_Hair017.name: Gaping Maw
WI_Hair017.description: She imagined looking down from the ceiling, her many eyes blinking as she watched her captors enter the room.

WI_Hair01_01.name: Stumpy Dreads (Marrow)
WI_Hair01_01.description: Tangled dreads marred with sap and clay.

WI_Hair01_02.name: Stumpy Dreads (Chalky)
WI_Hair01_02.description: Tangled dreads marred with soil and clay.

WI_Hair01_03.name: Overgrowth Affliction
WI_Hair01_03.description: Her head crawled with pain as sprouts twisted within, brightening her with leafy hues.

WI_Hair03_02.name: Dreaded Husks
WI_Hair03_02.description: These spurs are hardened outgrowths protruding from the skull. They resemble the horns of the unfortunate wildlife that have found themselves trapped in the swamps.

WI_Head01_4A.name: Crown of The Entity
WI_Head01_4A.description: A crown emanating a festive and ominous aura created by The Entity’s biggest fan.

WI_Head01_5A.name: 5th Anniversary Crown
WI_Head01_5A.description: A crown crafted for a very special anniversary.

WI_Head04_01.name: Exposed Floret (Grey / Blue)
WI_Head04_01.description: This compound arrangement across the head provides both, a hard outer covering as well as an attractive cluster of plant-based material.

WI_outfit_006_01.name: Delicate Garments
WI_outfit_006_01.description: Baubles and finery were hard to come by in her quaint little village.

WI_outfit_007.name: Snake Charmer
WI_outfit_007.description: Reeking of blood and rotting serpent meat, there’s the husk of a woman somewhere beneath it.

WI_outfit_008.name: Scorched Harvester
WI_outfit_008.description: She escaped when a charm of strength buried within her was ignited by the serum.

WI_outfit_009.name: The Abomination
WI_outfit_009.description: Her grandmother warned her not to trifle with such power...

WI_outfit_010.name: The Birch Witch
WI_outfit_010.description: The wind blew and whispered, a warm breath that stirred an ancient power within her.

WI_outfit_011.name: Swamp Creature
WI_outfit_011.description: She emerged from the foul dark marshes, stinking of algae and rot… something from a lost realm had changed her.

WI_outfit_012.name: Toxic Roots
WI_outfit_012.description: Her body was exposed to foreign organisms in a deadly realm.

WI_outfit_014.name: Family Knowledge
WI_outfit_014.description: Her grandmother used to teach her survival lessons during long walks in the woods.

WI_outfit_015.name: Fetid Bloom
WI_outfit_015.description: Her body lay in a foul swamp for what felt like ages, straddling the blurry line between dream and reality.

WI_outfit_017.name: Black Widow
WI_outfit_017.description: Her little cellar was home to many dangerous creatures. She imagined joining them, learning their ways.

WI_outfit_01_03.name: Verdant Outbreak
WI_outfit_01_03.description: The rituals brought her closer to nature until, one day, she became one with it.

WI_outfit_03_01.name: Bile Beldam
WI_outfit_03_01.description: She relished in the darkness of the swamp, growing stronger as days turned into an endless night.

WI_outfit_04_01.name: Sapling Siren
WI_outfit_04_01.description: The transformation into full plant creature is almost complete. Just a few more souls to produce the light and energy required…

WI_W006.name: Golden Bands
WI_W006.description: Ornate bands, carved with symbols of power, encircle her talon.

WI_W006_01.name: Ringed Claw
WI_W006_01.description: She saw something shiny embedded in the mud before everything went black.

WI_W007.name: Voracious Talon
WI_W007.description: Squeezed tight by the body of a snake, moss grows fat on the twisted, fractured claw.

WI_W007_01.name: Garland Talon
WI_W007_01.description: A rotting garland of moss spread on the twisted and fractured claw.

WI_W008.name: Calcified Talons
WI_W008.description: The serum turned her flesh into hardened thorns.

WI_W009.name: Reach of Other
WI_W009.description: The ferocity of her claw was given new life by the tumorous growth that formed from it.

WI_W010.name: Gnarled Talon
WI_W010.description: Her bond with nature empowered her to tear her assailants apart.

WI_W011.name: Amphibious Claws
WI_W011.description: Just as capable of rending flesh on land as they are at sea.

WI_W012.name: Wooden Clamps
WI_W012.description: A lethal claw produced by a merciless nature.

WI_W013.name: Sugared Claws
WI_W013.description: Devastating claws with shards of sugar glass embedded in the skin.

WI_W014.name: Piercing Thorn
WI_W014.description: The moss-covered woman had limbs like tree branches and a rough grip.

WI_W015.name: Backwater Sting
WI_W015.description: There was a wretched, violent beauty in the thing that she had become.

WI_W017.name: Venomous Claw
WI_W017.description: She would feel the life drain from them slowly, painfully, until they stopped fighting back.

WI_W01_03.name: Venus Grip
WI_W01_03.description: A sticky fluid oozed from her pores as her claw felt more like a merciless clamp.

WI_W03_01.name: Toxic Talon
WI_W03_01.description: The talon supports both, the injection of poisons and toxins, as well as the removal of liquids, such as blood.

WI_W04_01.name: Entangled Thorn (Light Purple / Ice Blue)
WI_W04_01.description: A tangled mess of intertwined stems and shoots that have formed into a sharp, rigid spike. Like a root, it can drain and absorb liquid from whatever it is lodged in for long enough.

WO_001.name: Tracking Device
WO_001.description: Always be aware of your surroundings.

WR_Head01_01.name: "Swift Strikes" - White
WR_Head01_01.description: The Kuntin-Wehye symbol, representing rapid and deadly aggressions, is finger-drawn in white paint.

WR_Head01_02.name: "The Owl" - White
WR_Head01_02.description: The Ug-Wufo symbol, representing a flying hunter of the night, is finger-drawn in white paint.

WR_Head01_Halloween.name: All Hallows' Eyes
WR_Head01_Halloween.description: Something wicked pierces the shadows of this frightful night.

WR_Machete02_Addon01.name: Skull Crusher
WR_Machete02_Addon01.description: Sharpened, rusty car parts bound to the bone make each hit more visceral.

XI_001.name: Enigmatic Glyph
XI_001.description: An unusual glyph that hints at a mystery within.

XI_002.name: Amplified Glyph
XI_002.description: An activated glyph, buzzing with a dangerous energy.

XI_003.name: Stabilized Glyph
XI_003.description: A temporarily stable glyph, opening to something far beyond our understanding.

XI_004.name: Chaotic Glyph
XI_004.description: A glyph overwhelmed with unstable energy, breaking under the weight of existence.

XI_005.name: Lucky Chip
XI_005.description: A keychain that Ace used as a card guard during one of his biggest Texas hold'em scores.

XI_006.name: Stopped Stopwatch
XI_006.description: It's a stopwatch that takes its name far too literally.

XI_007.name: Uh, Oh's Shot Glass
XI_007.description: Uh, Oh's Pub & Grill is the place to be for off-beat and unusual Vegas bets.

XI_008.name: Meg Thomas Figurine
XI_008.description: Fast out of the gates, Meg's sprint burst earned her a shiny gold medal.

XI_009.name: Trey Aces
XI_009.description: If you ever need an ace up your sleeve, here's three.

XI_010.name: The Calamitous Bell
XI_010.description: Run while the bell tolls, run o soul forsaken.

XI_011.name: Catalyst of Madness
XI_011.description: In the ashes, the embers burn red hot.

XI_012.name: Sizzling Grill
XI_012.description: A well-used grill smelling of blood and meat.

XI_013.name: Yesterday's Sandals
XI_013.description: A melancholy image of sandals, worn during simpler, care-free days.

XI_014.name: Magnificent Conch
XI_014.description: An uninhabited shell like many others, yet spectacular nonetheless.

XI_015.name: Wormy Opener
XI_015.description: And this is why you don't open cans of worms.

XI_016.name: Can of Worms
XI_016.description: General wisdom states that a can of worms should never be opened, yet here we are.

XI_017.name: Marshmallow Branch
XI_017.description: A stalk of wood vastly improved with the addition of high sugar treats.

XI_018.name: Autohaven Wreckers
XI_018.description: We'll wreck anything you bring in—no questions asked.

XI_019.name: Blackened Catalyst
XI_019.description: What appears as a benign symbol can hold the very power of death.

XI_020.name: Death Wreck
XI_020.description: It's a wrecked car or, from another point of view, an affordable coffin made of reliable American steel.

XI_021.name: Tiki Death Cup
XI_021.description: A refreshing summer beverage that carries a terrible curse.

XI_022.name: Grimy Shackles
XI_022.description: In these restraints her spirit broke, until all that remained was a terrible hunger.

XI_023.name: Playful Poltergeist
XI_023.description: For all the trauma that existed in the world, he was still a child with childish hopes.

XI_024.name: Startled Poltergeist
XI_024.description: When the men came, he only knew to do one thing—hide.

XI_025.name: Vengeful Poltergeist
XI_025.description: He killed the men for what they did. He made them howl in pain.

XI_026.name: Roaming Poltergeist
XI_026.description: He wanted to believe that things in a new land could be better.

XI_027.name: Wrathful Poltergeist
XI_027.description: Wrath overcame him, but even then he resisted—until something unknown, something unnatural, twisted him.

XI_028.name: Backstreet Champ
XI_028.description: She moved fast through the alleys, but how far could speed take her?

XI_029.name: Fledgling Champ
XI_029.description: She had a lot to learn before the track meet and not a lot of time to learn it.

XI_030.name: School Champ
XI_030.description: She might just be the fastest in her school, but she'd have to prove it.

XI_031.name: Broken Champ
XI_031.description: She was so close to her goal, but an injury stopped her dead in her tracks.

XI_032.name: State Champ
XI_032.description: She gritted her teeth through injury and persevered over all.

XR_002.name: MOBA Mouse
XR_002.description: The biggest names in esports have sported this brand.

XR_003.name: Hiro Figurine
XR_003.description: A collector's item produced with high-quality 3d printing.

XR_005.name: Hiro Poster
XR_005.description: Kids still put posters like these on their bedroom walls.

XR_006.name: Dinoid Figurine
XR_006.description: A collector's item painted entirely by hand.

XR_008.name: Game Case
XR_008.description: Many collectors seek out physical copies of this game.
